    "comment": "Rationale: The authors use the lamprey reticulospinal synapse. They inject an antibody (function blocking) into the pre synapse. They stimulate the neurons for 30 min at 5 Hz to activate SV exo/endocytosis. In the antibody injected neurons there is a large accumulation of clathrin-coated tubules.\n\n15/8/2017 Pim\n- The lamprey accession was found via Blast of the human EHD1 protein. Experimental description: From the abstract, \"We have investigated the role of an EHD1/3 ortholog (l-EHD) in the lamprey giant reticulospinal synapse\"",
